				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Points and Charms<a name="26806"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 10 04 6:13 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Maybe this has been done before and if it has please just post a link. I recently got LDoN after a long break from EQ and I'm a little hazy how charms work. I bought a 6 pt charm from ldon merchant and auged it with my stone, but no stats or anything yet so i don't care if i have to destroy it. Some people tell me i should get a figurine cause they say when i get my pop flags stats will increase on it but not if it's an ldon charm. Does the ldon charm itself have stats added to it, or is it your adventure stone? 
<br />

<br />
I'm also unclear as to how pts are shared with other camps if they are at all. This may make a good guide, or maybe the answers are so simple you're all laughing at me secretly, lol. Thanks in advance for the great info.</span></td>
