				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Points and Charms<a name="26840"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 10 04 10:08 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>The cheap charms that can be purchased from the merchants have stats when you zone into a LDoN dungeon. The adventure's stone itself will increase as you learn the lore of the different dungeons (essentially, winning missions and talking to NPCs at the camps and elsehwere).
<br />

<br />
As far as points, I will try to explain it. When you win a mission, you get points based on the difficulty of the dungeon (determined by the average level of the group), and your own level. These points go directly to your generic Adventure Point pool, which can be spent to buy items and augmentations from the Adventure Merchants at the camps. These points are also used as 'favor points' which allows you to access higher level items from the adventure merchants. Favor points are theme specific and are not depleted as you buy items; after you win enough missions at a camp to access a specific level of items (for example, 1492, the max), you will always have access to the highest level of items from that camp, even if you don't have enough adventure points to buy anything.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">&nbsp;&nbsp;Hunter Sirioh <br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;Impresario Arafein Sinofei<br>
